      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get the point about gentrification, but it feels like the people who oppose higher density are usually just using those concerns as an excuse to maintain NIMBYism and keep neighborhoods exclusive. shouldn't the priority just be moving toward these denser, more sustainable models instead of getting bogged down by the arguments of groups that are basically just trying to stop progress?",
