      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The opposition to density is often rooted in deeply ingrained desires for neighborhood preservation and community character, which are legitimate concerns for residents. While NIMBYism certainly plays a role, dismissing all opposition ignores valid worries about infrastructure strain and the loss of local identity. A successful path forward involves thoughtful, incremental density increases coupled with strong community engagement to mitigate negative impacts, rather than simply pushing through rapid change.",
      "source": "target",
